      <section eId="sec_60_20">
        <num>60.20</num>
        <heading>Authorized dispositions; traffic infraction</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_20__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A period of conditional discharge, as provided in article\nsixty-five; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_20__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Unconditional discharge as provided in section 65.20; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_20__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A fine or a sentence to a term of imprisonment, or both, as\nprescribed in and authorized by the provision that defines the\ninfraction; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_20__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A sentence of intermittent imprisonment, as provided in article\neighty-five.\n  2. Where a sentence of conditional discharge is imposed for a traffic\ninfraction, all incidents of the sentence shall be the same as would be\napplicable if the sentence were for a violation.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
